Fourth: Active Directory Domain Services
On the right top side, choose manage -> Add Roles and Features
Next - > keep the Role-based or feature-based installation - > next

Then, server selection, it show your current virtual network, 
in server role, add Active Directory Domain Services.
then continue on, there is no other configuration
Then install and wait.

After complete, stage two, promote the server to Domain controller

Click Promote this server to a domain controller
Step 1:Deployment Configuration
Choose Add a new forest 
In name : lab.local
Next
Step 2: Domain Controller Options
It will tick the Domain Name System (DNS) server , which will install DNS service for you

Then will be password, i use P@ssword123 again

next
Step 3:
In DNS, it will notify a warning, next to skip that
Step 4:
Keep the name and next

Step 5: Path ( storage path)
Kept the default setting and next
Step 6: Review Options
